I actually think this is where your "braided" metaphor becomes mathematically interesting.

Instead of a taxonomy (tree)...

Pantheon is much closer to a **fiber bundle** or **hypergraph**.

Every concept simultaneously exists in many dimensions.

"Tiger" isn't stored once.

It's the intersection of dozens of manifolds.

That's remarkably similar to how modern embedding spaces behave. A word isn't stored in one category; it's represented by its position relative to many overlapping semantic dimensions.

